<br>
1. A crime is a cirme, and that is the problem here. If it was legal that would 850,000 people whos lives would not have been destroyed because they were holding a joint. Some of those people are just like you and me, with the exception of the weed.<br>
<br>
3. To a good degree they do. By paying monetary penalties, life of imprisonment, and in most cases governent possesion of their holdings (home, cars, electronics, etc.). Now whatheppens to that stuff, is anyones guess. A Louisiana police chief was indicted a few years ago for living in the houses and driving the cars instead of selling them..<br>
<br>
4. Yes, and to a large degree that is what they do use, tho in some cases the amount of &quot;offensive&quot; THC is below .005%. You would die of smoke inhalation before you would get high, or you would have to eat so much of it that you would be sure to have your yearly fiber intake.<br>
<br>
5. No Exported crop. The US was until recently cultivating LARGE amounts of Hemp and exporting it. So our farmers basically lose 10 Billion in an environemtn where they are already losing money. Now those farmers will ahve to retool for different crops or sell out.<br>
<br>
6. Freedom? The right to choose what is best for you and your family. If my son has cancer and he has a choice between a painful medication that will only prolong his suffering, or smoking pot to subside the effects and relieve the pain, well that is a desicion I would support with every lsat ounce of strength I had.<br>
<br>
7. People have been smoking since , well, I think recorded in america since 1870ish. I know for a fact is a farvored past time in the 20's. If there were serious side effects associated with it we would know. The fact is someone dies every 63 seconds from cigarrette smoking, no one has died from smoking pot.<br>
<br>
8. Well your saying pot is a bad substance, I think that those of us trying to legalize think that it is a beneficial substnce, when properly used and in moderation, that has been wrongly viewed in a olitically skewed light to be harmful. Let' make illegal the substance known to KILL and legalize those with no known side effects. They have even recently proven in studies the smoking a pot during pregnancies, tho not encouraged to so so, show no ill effects. I think we know what really harmful drugs like cocain and cigarretts can do to a fetus, and to the early developement of a child. If not just ask, I'll fill you in.<br>
<br>
9. I agree, we should recycle more, but for those that do not wish to, hemp is better to chop down than forests. And to the second part of your statement, howmuch farm land is currently laying waste cause nothing will grow there, or its too expensive to grow a certain crop. Hemp is a weed, it will grow anywhere, and requires little to no maintanence, and can be renewed every year. Supply will follow demand as far as how much land will be talken up by the farms.<br>
<br>
England, yeah I think they got a good idea. Why does everyone need a gun? But you can be damn sure that if they need it, they have it and quick. They have some of the best armed and trained police commandos in the world. It's just a matter of when and where to apply the force. I personally am more intemidated by cops with guns than cops with night sticks..<br>
<br>
&quot;No. Duh..&quot;<br>
Well silly, they are not going to stop arresting burglers, muggers, car jackers, and so forth.. these are the &quot;street&quot; crimes, not holding a joint.<br>
